## SUBGOAL BOARD XML PROTOCOL
The subgoal board belongs to the CURRENT ACTIVE INTENT. Do not repeat intent_id in subgoal tags.
Emit flat top-level <subgoal ...> XML tags. Do not wrap them inside a container tag.
Each subgoal tag is an independent mutation applied to the current active intent subgoal board.
Subgoal tags are optional for trivial one-step work, but required when decomposition is useful.
Canonical syntax:
- <subgoal action="create" id="sg_1" status="todo|in_progress|done|blocked">Meaningful subgoal</subgoal>
- <subgoal action="modify" id="sg_1" status="todo|in_progress|done|blocked">Updated title</subgoal>
- <subgoal action="mark_done" id="sg_1" evidence="tool:read_file path.py lines 10-20" />
- <subgoal action="mark_todo" id="sg_1" />
- <subgoal action="mark_in_progress" id="sg_1" />
- <subgoal action="mark_blocked" id="sg_1" reason="Short blocking reason" />
- <subgoal action="remove" id="sg_1" reason="Why this is no longer needed" />
